    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-29T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-29T02:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6331/177: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-29T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 29, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>329. Reference Legation’s 327, July 27, 3 p.m.<note n="59" xml:id="d568fn59">Not
                        printed.</note> and Department’s 231, July 27, 6 p.m., following from
                    Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 28, 5 p.m. I was informed this afternoon by the Japanese Consul
                            General that Tsuchiyama is being today deported from Mukden to Japan
                            under escort of relatives and police. Upon arrival at his native village
                            he will be subject to special observation by the <pb facs="0767" n="677"
                                xml:id="pg_677"/> police authorities there who will decide whether
                            confinement in asylum or home is necessary. I will shortly transmit a
                                despatch<note n="59a" xml:id="d568fn59a">Not printed.</note>
                            containing additional information concerning the legal and anti-American
                            aspects of the case and suggest advisability of Embassy’s deferring
                            action pending its receipt.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
